        <descriptionSet>
            <description>Flannery O'Connor's first novel  Wise Blood was published in 1952. That same year, Brainard Cheney, a Southern writer living in Nashville and associated with the literary movement known as the Agrarians, wrote an appreciative review which prompted  O'Connor to send a letter thanking  Cheney. Thus began a correspondence and friendship with Cheney and his wife Francis that lasted many years. The letters, housed in Vanderbilt Special Collections  are collected in this volume. </description>
